# Content Data

Keep all display content in `src/data/` — components should import, not hardcode.

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `experiences.ts` | Work history (**generated** from `career/content/experiences.yaml` via `yarn career:generate`) |
| `swProjects.ts` | Software projects |
| `artProjects.ts` | Art portfolio items |
| `technologies.ts` | Skills/tech stack icons |
| `navigation.ts` | Navbar links |
| `colors.ts` | Color constants |

Experience bullets are edited in `career/` (YAML or `yarn career:ui`), not by hand in `experiences.ts`. See [`career/README.md`](../../career/README.md).

Define TypeScript types in `src/types/` (e.g., `experience.types.ts`, `project.types.ts`). Export named constants with full metadata (company, duration, technologies, URLs, etc.).

Assets referenced from data go in `src/assets/` (SVG for icons/logos, WebP for photos).
